        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 11:54PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1153 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Calf Creek to near Us-377 Near The Kimble-
Menard County Line to 6 miles north of Segovia. Movement was east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Art, The Intersection Of Us-
190 And Ranch Road 1311, Yates Crossing, Saline, Streeter, Us-
377 Near The Kimble-
Menard County Line, Camp Air, Hilda, The Intersection Of Highway 29
And Ranch Road 1222, Us-190 Near The Menard-
Mcculloch County Line, Cleo, Calf Creek, Grit, Us-83 Near The Kimble-
Menard County Line, Katemcy, Junction, Voca, Erna, Fredonia, and Camp
San Saba.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 451 and 460, and
near Mile Marker 468.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
